Migrate legacy Localhost host encoding in pod DB

The Podman support changes turned Host::Localhost into a struct variant
carrying an engine field. Pod records written by earlier versions store
the host column as the JSON string "Localhost", which the new variant
no longer deserializes, so any operation on such pods failed with
"invalid type: unit variant, expected struct variant".

Rewrite legacy rows to the current encoding when opening the database.
ContainerEngine::Auto prefers Docker, so migrated pods keep targeting
the Docker engine they were created with, matching how legacy Ssh rows
already default their engine field.
